DATA CLOUD
Enhance Data with Insights

The insights features let you define and calculate multidimensional metrics from your entire digital state stored in Data Cloud.

Your metrics can include customer lifetime value (LTV), Most Viewed Categories, and customer satisfaction score (CSAT) at the profile, segment, population level, or any other desired specialized metrics.

After creating your insights, put them into effect for your streaming insights with data actions.

Calculated Insights
You can use a calculated insight to define and calculate multidimensional metrics on your entire digital state in Data Cloud. You can create metrics at the profile, segment, and population levels. For example, you can evaluate performance at the channel level or use product metrics to understand purchasing and browsing behavior.
Streaming Insights
Get insights more quickly by creating metrics on streaming data. Streaming insights are aggregation queries based on real-time engagement data for a rolling time window. The data is processed from streaming data sources such as Web SDK and Mobile SDK. You can use a streaming insight to build time series aggregation in near real time that can be used to drive orchestration or data actions in Data Cloud.
Real-Time Insights
Use real-time insights to build more complex personalization logic for your website. Real-time insights allow you track cumulative website activity to see if the user’s activity meets defined thresholds.
Validate an Insight in Data Cloud
After creation, validate your calculated or streaming insight in Data Explorer to ensure that your data and formulas are accurate. You must validate an insight before you use it in a segment.
Data Types in Insights
To enhance data compatibility and increase flexibility, use data types when adding an aggregate function to define a calculated or streaming insight SQL statement. The aggregate function calculates a set of values and returns a single value in Data Cloud. When using an aggregate function, you must specify a measure and dimension.
How Are Calculated, Streaming, and Real-Time Insights Different?
Calculated insights, streaming insights, and real-time insights can be used in different ways to make the most of your data. Use the comparison table to decide which one is best for you.
Visual Insight Builder
Create metrics in Data Cloud using the intuitive Visual Insight Builder UX tool.
